4. Helen Schucman scribed the words of an inner voice that she attributed to Jesus, which formed the basis of her 1976 best-selling self-study course. In each case, Taves argues, the sense of a guiding presence emerged through a complex, creative interaction between a founding figure with unusual mental abilities and an initial set of collaborators who were drawn into the process by diverse motives of their own.A major work of scholarship, this compelling and accessible book traces the very human processes behind such events.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aExperience (Religion)vCase studies. 0aMormon Church. 0aRevelationvCase studies. 0aSpiritual lifevCase studies. 0aSpiritualityvCase studies. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066259708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package 2017z978311063881340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400884469zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400884469.jpg  a978-3-11-063881-3  PUP eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066259-7  PUP eBook-Package 2016-2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA21UPPPUP  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aPDA9PRIN